description:
src/lib.rs:115-125 the credential-mode match block is reasonable but inlines what is logically a small parser. Could extract:

  fn parse_credential_mode(s: Option<&str>) -> Result<CredentialMode, SecretError> {
      match s {
          None | Some("chained") => Ok(CredentialMode::Chained),
          Some("managed-identity") => Ok(CredentialMode::ManagedIdentity),
          Some("developer") => Ok(CredentialMode::Developer),
          Some(other) => Err(SecretError::InvalidUri(format!("unknown credential mode `{other}`; supported: managed-identity, developer, chained (default)"))),
      }
  }

This is taste with no engineering basis — flagged as opinion. Filed for completeness; do not treat as a required fix.
